The paper deals with generating realistic images of faces with missing context and background pixels, which falls under the category of computer vision (cs.CV). The use of GANs for image synthesis and the focus on generating realistic images also suggests the sub-categories of graphics (cs.GR) and multimedia (cs.MM). The paper also mentions the use of perceptual and identity preserving losses, which are common in deep learning approaches for image recognition and classification, indicating the sub-categories of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG).
